    description: `Holnak Toofan (Qissa Syedna Nooh) is the third volume in the Silsila Qasas ul Anbiya series, presenting the story of Prophet Nooh (Noah), peace be upon him, in a captivating and child-friendly format. Prophet Nooh holds a significant place in Islamic tradition as one of the five prophets of great resolve (Ulul Azm) and as the prophet who preached to his people for an extraordinarily long period, spanning centuries, making his story one of the most powerful examples of patience, perseverance, and dedication in the history of prophethood. The title "Holnak Toofan" (The Terrible Flood) refers to the great deluge that Allah sent upon the disbelievers of Nooh's community, an event that is mentioned in the Quran and is familiar to readers of all Abrahamic faiths. The book narrates Nooh's story in simple and engaging Urdu, making it accessible and enjoyable for young readers. It begins with the state of Nooh's people, who had fallen into idol worship and abandoned the teachings of the earlier prophets. The book describes Nooh's initial efforts to call his people to the worship of Allah alone, his patient preaching over many years, the various methods he used to reach his community, and the stubborn opposition he faced from the arrogant leaders of his people. The building of the ark (safina) under Allah's instructions is described in a manner that captures children's imagination, explaining how Nooh constructed the vessel despite the mockery and ridicule of his people. The dramatic scenes of the great flood, the boarding of the ark by the believers and the animals, the destruction of the disbelievers, and the eventual grounding of the ark on Mount Judi are narrated with vivid detail that brings the story to life. Throughout the narrative, the book emphasises the moral lessons that children can learn from Nooh's story, including the importance of remaining patient when facing opposition, the virtue of persistence in doing good, the consequences of arrogance and disbelief, and the mercy of Allah towards those who believe in Him. The story also teaches children about the destructive nature of following false leaders and the importance of heeding the guidance of righteous teachers. As part of the thirty-volume series on the prophets, this book is an essential component of any child's Islamic library.`,
