    slug: "how-the-prophet-muhammad-peace-be-upon-him-performed-hajj",
    description: `How the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) Performed Hajj is a detailed and authoritative guide to the rituals of Hajj based entirely on the authentic narrations of the Prophet's farewell pilgrimage. This book holds a special place in the literature of Hajj because it reconstructs the exact manner in which Prophet Muhammad performed the pilgrimage during his only Hajj, known as Hajjat al-Wada (the Farewell Pilgrimage), which took place in the tenth year of the Hijrah. Since the Prophet's performance of Hajj serves as the primary model for all Muslims, understanding the precise details of how he performed each ritual is essential for anyone who wishes to complete the pilgrimage in accordance with the Sunnah. The book follows a chronological structure, guiding the reader through each stage of the Prophet's Hajj in the order in which it was performed, from the moment the Prophet assumed ihram in Madinah to the final tawaf al-ifadah before returning home. Each ritual is described in meticulous detail, including the exact words and supplications recited by the Prophet at each stage, drawn from authentic hadith narrations in the major collections of Bukhari, Muslim, and other reliable sources. The book covers the assumption of ihram and the accompanying intentions, the entry into Makkah and the tawaf of arrival, the sa'i between Safa and Marwa, the journey to Mina, the standing at Arafat with the Prophet's sermon, the journey to Muzdalifah, the stoning of the pillars at Mina, the sacrifice, the shaving of the head, the tawaf al-ifadah, the return to Mina for the days of tashriq, and the final farewell tawaf. Where there are differences of scholarly opinion regarding the details of any ritual, the author presents the relevant evidence and explains the basis for each view, allowing the reader to understand the reasoning behind different practices. The book also includes practical guidance for modern pilgrims, addressing contemporary issues such as accommodation, transportation, and the management of large crowds, while maintaining its focus on the authentic Prophetic methodology. Written in clear and accessible English, this guide is an essential companion for anyone intending to perform Hajj or Umrah, as well as for students of Islamic jurisprudence who wish to study the fiqh of pilgrimage in detail. The comprehensive coverage, reliance on authentic sources, and practical approach make this one of the most reliable Hajj guides available in the English language.`,
    metaDescription: "How the Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) Performed Hajj provides an authentic step-by-step guide to Hajj rituals based on the farewell pilgrimage narrations."
